Description: Fragment of oval handle from a probably Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine micaceous purplish brown. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and prow symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Philokrates. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 28a, 25
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0243)
